,"text":"query return the relation from the closure, e.g. align(..) { $0.parent }."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The relation must be the same type as the item type. If this is a problem"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"then cast the query to the most general type, e.g. "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"treat(as:UIView.self)"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Providing one quadrantal will align both items and anchor on that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"quadrantal position. Providing an additional anchor quadrantal will"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"align the item quadrantal (at that quadrantal position) to the anchor"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"quadrantal (at that quadrantal position)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"For example, align(.A2) will align the .A2 position of each item to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the .A2 position of the anchor item."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Wheras, align(.A2, with:.C3) will align the .A2 position of each item"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to the .C3 position (center) of the anchor item."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Positive offsets add spacing "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"away"}]},{"type":"text","text":" from origin (toward bottom-trailing)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Offset respects layout direction (i.e. it goes "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"toward"}]},{"type":"text","text":" origin"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"on the horizontal axis)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"“Offset” is not to be confused with “insets”."}],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"conformance":{"constraints":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"B"},{"type":"text","text":" conforms to "